title: Devotees throng Puri to witness ‘Bahuda Yatra’
text:
Other Articles "Break Ke Baad" director's next is a thriller produced by Ekta Kapoor Emraan Hashmi begins shooting for 'Azhar' Katrina Kaif in 'no hurry' to marry beau Ranbir Kapoor Thousands of devotees on Sunday thronged the holy city of Puri to witness the world-famous Bahuda Yatra, the return car festival, of the deities – lord Jagannath, lord Balabhadra, lord Sudarshan and Devi Subhadra.
The ‘Chhera Pahanra’ by Gajapati Dibyasingh Deb of Puri is slated for 2.30 p.m. to 3.30 p.m. today and the pulling of the chariots is scheduled to begin by 4 p.m. this evening.
Meanwhile, elaborate security arrangements have been made for the Bahuda Yatra.
 26, 2015 4:00 pm
